WorldStage NewsOnline—-The All Progressives Congress (APC) in Sokoto on Sunday promised to retrieve its stolen mandate from the People Democratic Party (PDP) in the state. Alhaji Yusuf Suleiman, Director General APC Gubernatorial Campaign Organisation in Sokoto who disclosed this in an interview lauded members of the party for coming out  to vote for the party’s candidates  in the just concluded general elections. The party’s candidate Ahmed Aliyu narrowly lost the governorship post to incumbent Aminu Tambuwal of the Peoples Democratic Party. But in this interview, Suleiman, a former minister, said the APC has filed a petition at the tribunal to retrieve what he called ‘the stolen  mandate’. “We won the election but INEC and PDP in Sokoto rigged the elections”, he said.